    {
        "content": "<p>Would phrasing like 'Their sent messages' work?</p>",
        "id": 857132,
        "sender_full_name": "Neil Pilgrim (neiljp)",
        "timestamp": 1587271188
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How about: (in terms of code) we count the number of characters in a user's name and make a decision based on that.</p>\n<p>Also, how long (in characters) are usernames in general? What's the maximum length?</p>",
        "id": 857171,
        "sender_full_name": "Yash RE",
        "timestamp": 1587281877
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We want to avoid conditionally showing names.</p>",
        "id": 857209,
        "sender_full_name": "Steve Howell",
        "timestamp": 1587286663
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>avoiding names can help in avoiding the varying  width of popovers</p>",
        "id": 857214,
        "sender_full_name": "Siddharth",
        "timestamp": 1587287922
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"58\">Steve Howell</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/101-design/topic/.22View.20messages.20sent.22.20in.20user.20popover/near/857209\" title=\"#narrow/stream/101-design/topic/.22View.20messages.20sent.22.20in.20user.20popover/near/857209\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We want to avoid conditionally showing names.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Why though? Consistency reasons?</p>\n<p>re: width, in almost all typefaces <code>W</code> is the widest character, and <code>I</code> is the least wide, so you can perform some shoddy calculations on the basis of that. Maybe this is relevant to only sans-serif fonts though?</p>",
        "id": 857215,
        "sender_full_name": "Yash RE",
        "timestamp": 1587287975
    },
